{"questionId":"12139","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p><em>In this question you will explore possible models for the spread of an infectious disease</em></p>\n<p>An infectious disease has begun spreading in a country. The National Disease Control Centre (NDCC) has compiled the following data after receiving alerts from hospitals.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/0025233698dc6131cb33588b8d65d6d04ae8a12a.png\"></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\">A graph of <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"n\">\n  <mi>n</mi>\n</math></span> against <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"d\">\n  <mi>d</mi>\n</math></span>&nbsp;is shown below.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/c13964a53d69efdc0f59cf0e2cd757e469be254d.png\"></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\">The NDCC want to find a model to predict the total number of people infected, so they can plan for medicine and hospital facilities. After looking at the data, they think an exponential function in the form <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"n = a{b^d}\">\n  <mi>n</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mi>a</mi>\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mi>b</mi>\n      <mi>d</mi>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span> could be used as a model.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Use an exponential regression to find the value of <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"a\">\n  <mi>a</mi>\n</math></span>&nbsp;and of <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"b\">\n  <mi>b</mi>\n</math></span>, correct to 4 decimal places.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"a = 9.7782{\\text{,}}\\,\\,b = 1.7125\">\n  <mi>a</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>9.7782</mn>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>,</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mi>b</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>1.7125</mn>\n</math></span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>M1A1A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong>[3 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"12139","referenceCode":"EXM.3.AHL.TZ0.9a","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Use an exponential regression to find the value of a and of b , correct to 4 decimal places.","paper":"3","level":"HL","questionNumber":"a","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 3]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 2—Functions","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","SL 4.11—Expected, observed, hypotheses, chi squared, gof, t-test","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","AHL 4.13—Non-linear regression","Topic 2—Functions","SL 2.5—Modelling functions","Topic 2—Functions","SL 2.6—Modelling skills","Topic 2—Functions","AHL 2.9—HL modelling functions"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}